	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="">Nice horn</a> <a id="fs8" href="#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Tue, Oct 23rd 12:38 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=82901"><span id="Scholar">JackOfSpeed</span></a><br /><b><span id="Scholar">Scholar</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">69 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [4.60]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Wow - what a nice instrument. The STA helps out with hp, and you can really maximize your effectiveness by playing haste songs for your melee types - and you'd get the instrument bonus. On top of that, you slap a mob for an additional 150hp and interrupt any casting with the stun. This is indeed an uber bard item. Actually, this is probably the most effective instrument in the game (not counting the instrument capabilities of the epic).<br/>Kinda sux that the effect is AoE though - AoE's get good groups killed, because they wake mezzed mobs, and you might draw some mobs from a level above or below. <br/><br/>Singing Steel BP - 60k<br/>59 levels worth of powerleveling - 100k<br/>Getting your entire guild killed with the AoE from your dandy new horn - priceless </p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />"Its probably better to be fat than ugly. You can always get less fat, but there ain't no cure for ugly... except maybe beer."</td></tr>
